The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Poll reforms 

 New Delhi, Jan. 12 (PTI): The Centre is examining the Election Commissions proposals for electoral reforms, including compulsory maintenance of accounts by political parties, negative voting, exit/opinion polls and prohibition of surrogate advertisements.

 In a July 2004 letter to the Prime Minister, the chief election commissioner had sent the proposals, which also demanded constitutional protection for all of its members, an independent secretariat, rule-making authority for the panel and powers to decide on matters relating to disqualification under the Constitutions 10th Schedule.




